column5: So after day one  at Lake Okeechobee,Pro-angler Bob Izumi is in 141 place with 11lbs 2oz. In the Co-angler ,Montrealer Richard McCrory sits in 4th place with 19lbs. 11Oz,while Josyln Leung(Angling Outfitters)is in 112 with 8lbs 6 oz. First place has 35lbs 3 oz, and 52 teams had over 20 lbs.Lets go guys
Nice Jos is beating Bob and prolly in Bob's old boat LOL Man I wish I could fish a tourny on the big O HUGE bass in there .
How do you figure that? Different categories. Bob's total weight is 2 lbs 12 oz's more than Jos.
I believe it is Bobs old boat and it's one awesome craft. Hope they get some monsters in there!
Do you have a link to the results? I am pretty sure my neighbor is down there as well. Josh got him into the tourneys and he loves it now.
Here's some real time stuff on the FLW.  http://www.flwoutdoors.com/flwondemand.cfm
Thanks Roy. My neighbour is 43rd right now. Hope he does well.
A buddy of mine Glen Pickering is also down there and sits in 9th..he got to fish with the day 1 leader and was more than happy to net all 35 lbs for him! Including both 8 pounders!!!

I realized that after I posted talked to the guys at AA today they don't think Jos made the day 3 cut but Bob had a good bag and may cash a cheque and a guy from Oakville is doing really well to but I can't remember his name .
Yeah it's Bob's old boat and he didn't take it, he's fishing as a co-angler no boat required.
